<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:259px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:87.26%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/ambertvtropespic_7164.jpg" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/ambertvtropespic_7164.jpg" width="259" height="226"></div></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:259px;"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeliberatelyCuteChild" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeliberatelyCuteChild">He might be cute</a>, but he'll do <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues">whatever it takes for the shinies</a>.</div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p>You're a dragon... a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidAppealCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidAppealCharacter">young</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSlacker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSlacker">underachieving</a> dragon and your parents have just <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GetOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GetOut">kicked you out</a> of the nest for <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoattailRidingRelative" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoattailRidingRelative">eyeing their treasure hoard</a>. Now it is time for you to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheQuest" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheQuest">go out</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TreasureHunter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TreasureHunter">find your own coins, jewels, and magic items</a>. The problem with being young (and a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookDumb" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookDumb">bad student</a>) is that you don&#146;t always succeed in your quest to find treasure. To make matters worse <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheRival" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheRival">other young dragons</a> have received the boot as well and you must compete with them for the best loot.</p><p>Released in 2014 by <em><a class="urllink" href="http://epicslantpress.com">Epic Slant Press<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></em>, <em>Havok and Hijinks</em> is a four-player card game that pits Amber the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePowerOfTheSun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePowerOfTheSun">Sunlight Dragon</a>, Obsidian the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CastingAShadow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CastingAShadow">Dark Dragon</a>, Pearl the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Lunacy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Lunacy">Moonlight Dragon</a>, and Ruby the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayingWithFire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayingWithFire">Fire Dragon</a> against one another. To win you must use the Havok cards to find treasure and the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues">Hijinks cards</a> to disrupt the treasure quests of your competition, ensuring that your hoard is a coin above the rest.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>A new <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExpansionPack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExpansionPack">Expansion Pack</a> is currently in the works. The website is located <a class="urllink" href="http://havokandhijinks.com">here<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</p><p></p><h2> This game contains examples of</h2><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionGirl">Action Girl</a>: Any of the female Sodality Knights, adventurers, or marauders</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual">All There in the Manual</a>: The website is full of lore and backstories on various elements and characters.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguousGender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguousGender">Ambiguous Gender</a>: Gender assignment of the dragons seems arbitrary at best</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtifactOfAttraction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtifactOfAttraction">Artifact of Attraction</a>: If it's shiny, the dragons likely want it and will get it through any means possible.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtShift" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtShift">Art Shift</a>:<ul><li> There's a variety of artstyles heading the website's blog posts, though the cards themselves are generally consistent</li><li> The expansion set's art is a bit flatter, due to a new artist</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallASmeerpARabbit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallASmeerpARabbit">Call a Smeerp a "Rabbit"</a>: Money is all grouped under the name 'talons.'</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColorFailure" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColorFailure">Color Failure</a>: as per the "Without Pigment" card</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DistaffCounterpart" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DistaffCounterpart">Distaff Counterpart</a>: While the originals aren't gender-specific, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenderFlip" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenderFlip">four additional</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleSixtyThree" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleSixtyThree">dragon cards</a> were made for the kickstarter campaign...<ul><li> Salida (Amber)</li><li> Darach (Obsidian)</li><li> Ottokar (Pearl)</li><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><li> Marielle (Ruby)</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EmpathicEnvironment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EmpathicEnvironment">Empathic Environment</a>: the 'ready' side versus 'tired' of each Dragon's card.</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FinaglesLaw" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FinaglesLaw">Finagle's Law</a>: Any strategy can be ruined with one flip of the deck</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Griefer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Griefer">Griefer</a>: Many of the hijinks cards allow players to go this route</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PandaingToTheAudience" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PandaingToTheAudience">Panda-ing to the Audience</a>: The appropriately-named, "Pandemonium" card. <a class="urllink" href="http://www.havokandhijinks.com/site_files/30.png">Its art<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a><small>&loz;</small> depicts some giant pandas<span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note0p57s');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note0p57s" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note0p57s');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;">Technically, they're giant giant pandas, since "giant panda" is the proper name of "regular" pandas</span> rampaging through a village.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerEqualsRarity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerEqualsRarity">Power Equals Rarity</a>: the promotional Crystal Dragon cards allow you to choose any elemental affinity for a time</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PromotionalPowerlessPieceOfGarbage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PromotionalPowerlessPieceOfGarbage">Promotional Powerless Piece of Garbage</a>: averted with the Crystal Dragon cards, as explained above.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PurelyAestheticGender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PurelyAestheticGender">Purely Aesthetic Gender</a>: Skills are based solely on the dragons' element</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a>:<ul><li> If the print-and-play version is anything to go by, there's the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JokeItem" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JokeItem">junk treasure card</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Twilight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Twilight">Princess Bella</a>.</li><li> As well as version of the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WolvesAlwaysHowlAtTheMoon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WolvesAlwaysHowlAtTheMoon">3 Wolf Moon T-shirt</a> and the <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MemeticMutation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MemeticMutation">certain video</a> of a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EverythingsBetterWithRainbows" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EverythingsBetterWithRainbows">Double Rainbow</a>.</li><li> The 'Moonwalk' card looks <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/MichaelJackson" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/MichaelJackson">familiar</a> as well...</li><li> The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AmericanPickers" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AmericanPickers">'Vallhyn Pickers'</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IKnowWhatYouDidLastSummer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IKnowWhatYouDidLastSummer">'I Know What You Did Last Night'</a> cards.</li><li> With the extra kickstarter hijinks cards come the musically-themed cards <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/JohnDenver" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/JohnDenver">'Sunshine on My Shoulders'</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/PinkFloyd" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/PinkFloyd">'The Darkside of the Moon'</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/FrankSinatra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/FrankSinatra">'Blue Moon'</a>, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BillyJoel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BillyJoel">'We Didn't Start the Fire'</a></li></ul></li></ul><p></p><hr>
</div>
